"title": "1194: glory, divine and human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1194",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Through the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ, believers will finally be glorified. All human glory derives from God.</p>\n<h2>Human glory in the creation</h2>\n<h3>Human glory as God's intention</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:6-Heb2:7\">HEB 2:6–2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:4-Ps8:5\">PSA 8:4–8:5</a></p>\n<h3>People are created in God's image</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:1\">GEN 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:27\">GEN 1:26–1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:6\">GEN 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:7\">1CO 11:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:9\">JAS 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Human beings have precedence over the rest of creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:26\">MAT 6:26</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:24\">LUK 12:24</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:29-Matt10:31\">MAT 10:29–10:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:6-Luke12:7\">LUK 12:6–12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:12\">MAT 12:12</a></p>\n<h3>Human responsibility for creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:19-Gen2:20\">GEN 2:19–2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:28\">GEN 1:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:6-Ps8:8\">PSA 8:6–8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:8\">HEB 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:7\">JAS 3:7</a></p>\n<h2>Human glory diminished after the fall</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23\">ROM 3:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:3\">GEN 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:29\">ECC 7:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12\">ROM 5:12</a></p>\n<h2>The imperfect nature of human glory</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:24-1Pet1:25\">1PE 1:24–1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:6-Isa40:8\">ISA 40:6–40:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:10-Ps49:11\">PSA 49:10–49:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:16-Ps49:17\">PSA 49:16–49:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:15\">PSA 103:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:7-2Cor3:8\">2CO 3:7–3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:10\">2CO 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:13\">2CO 3:13</a></p>\n<h2>Human glory is given and taken by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps82:6-Ps82:7\">PSA 82:6–82:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:16\">EXO 9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:13\">1KI 3:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:12\">2CH 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:6-Jer27:7\">JER 27:6–27:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:37-Dan2:39\">DAN 2:37–2:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:29-Dan4:31\">DAN 4:29–4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:36\">DAN 4:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:11\">JHN 19:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1\">ROM 13:1</a></p>\n<h2>The temporary nature of the glory of the wicked</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:19\">PHP 3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:15\">ISA 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:25\">LUK 16:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:14-Rev18:17\">REV 18:14–18:17</a></p>\n<h2>The temptation associated with human glory</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:8-Matt4:9\">MAT 4:8–4:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:5-Luke4:7\">LUK 4:5–4:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:10\">2TI 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:15\">1JN 2:15</a></p>\n<h2>The uniqueness of God's glory</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:9-Job40:10\">JOB 40:9–40:10</a></strong> <em>God shows Job the impossibility of human beings attaining the perfection of God's glory.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:11\">EXO 15:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:24-1Chr16:28\">1CH 16:24–16:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:3-Ps96:7\">PSA 96:3–96:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:8\">ISA 42:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:11\">ISA 48:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's glory revealed to human beings</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:17\">EXO 24:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:10\">EXO 16:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps26:8\">PSA 26:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:25-Ezek1:28\">EZK 1:25–1:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:9\">LUK 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:55\">ACT 7:55</a></p>\n<h2>Glory is not to be sought from other human beings but from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:2\">MAT 6:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:23-Jer9:24\">JER 9:23–9:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:7\">HOS 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:41-John5:44\">JHN 5:41–5:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:3\">PHP 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:4-1Thess2:6\">1TH 2:4–2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:16\">JAS 4:16</a></p>\n<h2>It is a human duty to glorify God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:3\">PSA 34:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:3\">PSA 63:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:12\">PSA 86:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:37\">DAN 4:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:6\">ROM 15:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:3-Gal1:5\">GAL 1:3–1:5</a></p>\n<h2>Glory is restored to redeemed humanity by the death of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:30\">ROM 8:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:23\">ROM 9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:47-1Cor15:49\">1CO 15:47–15:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:10\">COL 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual glory is divinely given</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:22\">JHN 17:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:11\">PSA 84:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a></p>\n<h2>Glorification when Jesus Christ returns</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:4\">COL 3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:18\">ROM 8:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:21\">PHP 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:20\">1TH 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:2\">1JN 3:2</a></p>",
